Embark on a transformative journey with the 200 Hour Yoga Teacher Training Course in Rishikesh, the birthplace of yoga practice nestled along the sacred Ganga and beneath the majestic Himalayas.

This immersive 3 to 4-week residential program welcomes beginners and intermediate students eager to deepen their yoga knowledge and teaching skills. The course offers a rich blend of traditional Hatha, Ashtanga, and Vinyasa yoga styles alongside pranayama, meditation, yoga philosophy, anatomy, and teaching methodologies.

Under the mentorship of experienced Yoga Allianceâ€“certified instructors, you will engage in daily rigorous practice, study, and teaching practicums designed to build confidence and mastery. The serene spiritual environment, comfortable accommodation, and wholesome vegetarian meals create an ideal setting for holistic growth.

Graduates earn an internationally recognized Yoga Alliance RYT 200 certification, enabling them to teach yoga worldwide with authenticity and clarity. Beyond the techniques, this training invites personal transformation, self-awareness, and a lifelong connection to yoga as a way of life.
